node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jon Reyes in Queens, New York with @envyscooters, @jobyinc, and @ridenyc. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.
Photo by Jon Reyes in Queens, New York with @envyscooters. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: What an incredible morning. I’ve always pushed to learn more and be consistent. Today felt different. I’ve realized there’s a level of riding that’s far ahead of where I am now, which has motivated me to take things further. Grateful for my health and well being that keeps up with my progression. Thank you @marttikuoppa for helping me work toward unlocking my true potential. 🙏🏼 #flatland

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jon Reyes in New York, New York with @envyscooters. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text: No intentions of slowing down. Full of focus from here on. 🙏🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jon Reyes in Queens, New York with @envyscooters, @jobyinc, @isfscoot, and @ridenyc. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
💥Big News💥Flatland Scootering is now part of the @isfscoot ! It’s been a dream of mine to have a chance to prove myself in from of the world and now I have another reason to push my progression. “Flatland Scooter World Championship” this December 🥇

#scooter #flatland #jonreyes

node.text: 14 Million Views! This is incredible and I’m grateful for everyone who supports me and my career. Thanks to all who made this film possible. 🙏🏼 #RideNYC
